### Telemetry Requirements

**All apps must emit business events** to the `business_events` table with the following structure:
```typescript
{
  app: string,              // Service identifier
  env: string,              // production | development | staging
  eventName: string,        // Specific event type (see app requirements)
  ts: Date,                 // Event timestamp
  actorType: string,        // student | provider | system | anonymous
  actorId: string | null,   // User/provider ID (null for anonymous)
  requestId: string,        // Request tracing ID
  sessionId: string | null, // Session identifier
  properties: object        // Event-specific data (no PII)
}
```

**Emission Guidelines:**
- Use fire-and-forget emission with error capture
- Never block request paths on event emission
- Log emission failures but continue processing
- Include requestId for end-to-end tracing
- No PII in properties object

### Data Integrity
- Use sentinel values to distinguish "no data" from true zero
- Preserve requestId tracing across all operations
- Archive JSON and Markdown artifacts for audit trails
- Never fabricate or interpolate missing metrics
